# Black Hole Entropy — Physical Parameter Model
# Solar-mass black hole: S_BH ≈ 1.05×10^77 k_B (Bekenstein-Hawking)
# Area: A = 4π(2GM/c²)² ≈ 4.2×10^77 λ_p² (in Planck tiles)
# Paper reference: §6.5 Black Hole Entropy, §8 Demo Cases (VFR-304 family)
# Physics fix: F_collapse uses GRW volume suppression (deferred Fix 2b)
# Status: numerically verified (Bekenstein-Hawking formula, CODATA 2018)
ENTITY: SolarMassBH
CYCLE: CPL-3
FRAME: t ∈ [0, 1 WarpTick]
UNITS: Planck

ENTROPY S:
  evolve Boltzmann {
    init: 1.05e77
    max: 1.05e78
    scale: 1e20 Plaseconds
  }

STABILITY:
  metric D = exp(-alpha_D * |∇S| * t)

IF D(t) < 0.01:
  collapse {
    energy: E_hawking
    resolution: lambda_p
  }

ON cycle.end:
  S = S / (1 + alpha)
